Programms, which are called by aufruf.out, which can generate lambda_in calculations using the Oniom for P3HT:DIPBI.

Use:
aufruf.out lambda_in_oniom  equi_2000ps_500k.gro 38 DIPBI 449 DIPBI PBE0_6-31Gs_UFF  1 1 true    "  oniom(PBE0/6-31G*:UFF(QEq)) Opt(Tight,MaxMicroiterations=50000)"  6-31G#_CHelpG  el    6 45 43 50 638 752 1104  
OR


charge_transport_package lambda_in_oniom  gromacsinput.gro     Resid1  Resname1   Resid2   Resname2    foldername       _N   _G   submission    "  Gaussian09-Inputline  "                                           Folderfor_partial_charges   el/lo   NumberofNeighbours     List with Resids of neighbours                                                                            
charge_transport_package lambda_in_oniom  equi_2000ps_500k.gro 38      DIPBI      449      DIPBI       PBE0_6-31Gs_UFF    1   1   true          "  oniom(PBE0/6-31G*:UFF(QEq)) Opt(Tight,MaxMicroiterations=50000)"  6-31G#_CHelpG               el      6                      45 43 50 638 752 1104  

The foldername identifies the calculation. 
_N counts the charge transfer pairs.
_G counts the morphology frame.


lambda_in_setup_on_the_fly_oniom.sh
The calculations are implemented as an 'on-the-fly'-method.
The scripts sub-myg09-lambda_in_Kankra.sh  or   sub-myg09-lambda_in_moria.sh aid to submit the calculations on the clusters (Which need to be adapted by a new user).


GENERATE THE INPUT FILES
Usage: ./lambda_in_setup_on_the_fly_oniom.sh < monomerA.xyz monomerB.xyz inputline foldername zieldatei run_lambda_in subg09_logical oniom  >
Bsp. ./lambda_in_setup_on_the_fly_oniom.sh MolA.xyz MolB.xyz "UFF  Opt(Tight,MaxMicroiterations=30000) " MolA_MolB_B3LYP_6-31G+ results_lambda_in.dat run_lambda_in.sh true oniom
 logical=true fuer sofortiges Submittieren

SUBMISSION
sub-myg09-lambda_in_Kankra.sh  sub-myg09-lambda_in_moria.sh
  

RUN GAUSSIAN09 CALCULATIONS AND EVALUATE lambda_in OR lambda_in_ONIOM
The script run_lambda_in_V3.sh is intended to be called by aufruf.out.

Usage:  ./run_lambda_in_V3.sh monomerA monomerB foldername lambda_in_results.dat oniom_ok=[oniom/false] use_reiterations=[true/false] sub_g09=[sub_g09/false] 
Execute ./run_lambda_in_V3.sh in foldername/./run_lambda_in_V3.sh
Provide the name for monomerA.
Provide the name for monomerB.
Provide the foldername.
The output data will be stored in lambda_in_results.dat. 
Use oniom for Oniom calculations (Handles the Freeze lists of atoms in the enviroment).
One can use the use_reiterations, where the initial structures where optimised structures in neutral, negative, positive charged state of a molecule in order to restart a failed calculation automatically.
sub_g09 can use a submission to the HPC cluster. 

